Hello [~kanghoy], this issue is related that Guest user is requesting to unlock every time (DBM mode) when you change to this user. DBM mode is triggered when you start/restart device, so it is needed once per user, but Guest user is requesting every time. I was trying to find out if this behavior was changed in Android R AOSP, because Android Q requests only once (as expected), and I could reproduce this issue in Pixel R.

Updating the steps as the issue happens:
{panel:title=Steps|bgColor=#f5f5f5}
- Set Fingerprint + PIN for main, secondary and guest user;
- Restart the device;
- When the main user starts, it will show "Unlock for all features and data" and won't be able to use fingerprint;
- Unlock the user and change to secondary user, it will have the same behavior above;
- Unlock secondary user and return to main user, it won't show "Unlock for all features and data" (indicating that this user is unlocked);
- Go to secondary user again and will have the same behavior above;
- Go to Guest and select to continue with the same user;
- It will show "Unlock for all features and data" (and won't be able to use fingerprint), unlock it using PIN and go to main or secondary;
- Go again to Guest user and it will show again "Unlock for all features and data" (and won't be able to use fingerprint);
- You can repeat the last steps for Guest user and it will ever ask to PIN.
{panel}

Checking on KeyguardUpdateMonitor, I could realize that in Android R was added a new intent called *ACTION_USER_STOPPED*. This intent is being used here [KeyguardUpdateMonitor|https://sse.am.mot.com/r_source/xref/mr-r-qsh2020/frameworks/base/packages/SystemUI/src/com/android/keyguard/KeyguardUpdateMonitor.java#2144]. I added some logs in this method and when leave guest user it is putting false in mUserIsUnlocked, this value was obtained in [UserManager|https://sse.am.mot.com/r_source/xref/mr-r-qsh2020/frameworks/base/core/java/android/os/UserManager.java#2323]. So it is requesting PIN/Pattern/Password every time because of this value obtained by UserManager.

*Framework/HAL - CoreServices* could you help us checking why UserManager is returning false for Guest user, please?
Thank you!

*Note:* I reproduced this issue only in Guest users and to know if device is in DBM mode, it must show "Unlock for all features and data" in lockscreen.

